Yes, you can use Electron programmatically within a Node.js app to spawn the Electron binary. Here's an example:
javascript
const electron = require('electron');
const proc = require('node:child_process');

console.log(electron); // Prints the path to the Electron binary

// Spawn Electron as a child process
const child = proc.spawn(electron);

Note that this usage is within a Node.js app (not an Electron app) and is typically used to launch Electron.
